body_html: By the way, libcaffe2_protos.a is needed when building an executable linked to caffe2, for it provides caffe2::NetDef and so on, but it is not presented in the "installation list". Is it an intended behavior or a bug?

body: By the way, `libcaffe2_protos.a` is needed when building an executable linked to caffe2, for it provides `caffe2::NetDef` and so on, but it is not presented in the "installation list". Is it an intended behavior or a bug?
